        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 10:08PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1007 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 13 miles south of Waka to 16 miles northwest
of Miami to 6 miles west of Codman to Kingsmill. Movement was east
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pampa, Kingsmill, Lefors, Codman, Lora, and Miami.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
